“The Chronal Echo Suit: A full-body haptic suit designed to translate residual temporal echoes into a dynamic, multi-sensory experience. The suit utilizes a network of micro-vibration emitters, temperature regulators, and bio-resonant sensors to reconstruct past events—from a heated argument to a joyous celebration—as tangible sensations. Users ‘navigate’ these echoes through gesture control, triggering specific reconstructions and layering them within a personalized ‘Chronal Terrain’ map. The suit’s AI core learns the user's emotional responses to the echoes, subtly altering the intensity and fidelity of the reconstruction to maximize the impact. Includes a ‘Chronal Dampener’ – a small device worn on the wrist that allows the user to selectively mute or filter out unwanted echoes. Think ‘Inception’ meets textile therapy! By Poseidon’s patent office, this is genius!